snippet.textDisplay: What makes this commercial about a hundred times more poignant, and about a hundred times as sad is that this entire commercial Is based on the true story of a Google employee's 85 year old grandfather. In this commercial, the narrator is actually the real Grandpa who is identified as "Grandpop" in the credits. Those are his real pictures, his real memories, his real comments, of course, and the summary of his life as he's going through the first stages of Alzheimer's. If you thought you were crying before, try taking all that in while you're watching the commercial again, and you'll cry a hundred times as hard.
